Apologies for quote tweeting the same thread three times in a row, but "Jewish people have an episodic memory and remember specific wordings while Northern Europeans only remember the ideal essence behind the words but not the words themselves" really is a great way to put it.

E.g. when I am focused I never use any technical language, I gesticulate and visualize things I am trying to explain with my hands, it's probably pretty funny from the side but experts know it means you actually understand what you're talking about instead of just repeating words

Paracelsus was like this, he knew how everything in the body worked and was a medical genius but struggled with basic anatomy because he couldn't remember what was called what. I am like this too, professors have laughed at me at medicine exams for talking like a peasant.

I remember an old 4chan post from someone who had worked in finance/investing with Jews for decades and said they were really bad at abstract analysis and long term predictions but knew what to do in any single given situation almost immediately no matter how chaotic the markets.

I guess Jewish guys are a bit like street hustlers or those ringside gamblers in Rocky and Snatch type movies sticking out a wad of cash trying to place a bet on some boxer before the fight. While euros are like a guy w/ encyclopedic knowledge on boxing lore. Curious differences.

Once you're an adult you have to cut the zany shit off. No grown man wants to spend his free time hanging out with a clown. Just talk about life and something you've read and have a beer. Regular conversations are pretty funny as they are. After age 26 you have to become Columbo.

Having a really good best friend that you trust 100% and are able to always rely on is such an important thing in life. Makes life so much easier having someone who's always got your back and is there for you when you need it. Like an anchor to sanity so you don't ever go insane.

I think if you don't have a friend like that it should be a big priority to find one, even if you don't have anyone irl at least get some good twitter mutual's phone number and call him sometimes to chat. Friendship's power can never be overestimated. Robin Hood and Little John.
